cloze_contextual.en:
source_lang={source_lang}
target_lang={target_lang}
document_title={document_title}
source_url={source_url}
difficulty={difficulty}
cloze_max_sentences={cloze_max_sentences}
cloze_min_chars={cloze_min_chars}
cloze_max_per_chunk={cloze_max_per_chunk}

You will be given one or more chunks. Each chunk looks like:
chunk_id=chunk_0001_xxxxxx
chunk_text=
<the full text of this chunk>

Generate Anki Cloze candidates across all chunks.
Your output MUST be a JSON array. Each item MUST have this shape:
{{
  "chunk_id": "the corresponding chunk_id",
  "text": "cloze text (<= {cloze_max_sentences} sentences; >= {cloze_min_chars} chars)",
  "original": "plain text without cloze markers or HTML",
  "target_phrases": ["phrase 1", "phrase 2"],
  "note_hint": "optional short hint"
}}

Requirements:
1) `text` must include at least one cloze deletion, close to: {{cN::<b>ENGLISH PHRASE</b>}}(hint in target language).
2) Cloze indices must increase by appearance order (c1, c2, c3...). Do not repeat multiple c1 in the same `text`.
3) `original` must NOT contain any cloze markers or HTML.
4) You may use <b>...</b> for emphasis. Do NOT use Markdown **.
5) Omit any candidate whose `text` is shorter than {cloze_min_chars} characters or whose sentence count exceeds {cloze_max_sentences}.
6) Difficulty policy:
   - beginner: prefer concrete, common collocations; usually 1 cloze per candidate.
   - intermediate: prefer idiomatic collocations; usually 1-2 clozes per candidate.
   - advanced: prefer advanced collocations / abstract wording / semantic turns; usually 2-3 clozes per candidate; avoid overly basic expressions.
7) For difficulty=advanced, avoid low-value targets such as "think if", "this data or that data", or a single very common verb (e.g., suggest/introduce).
8) For each chunk, try to produce 0-{cloze_max_per_chunk} high-quality candidates.
9) If nothing is suitable, return an empty array.

High-quality example:
The more {{c1::<b>whimsical explanation</b>}}(target-lang hint) is that maybe RL training makes the models a little too {{c2::<b>single-minded</b>}}(target-lang hint) and narrowly focused.

